column5: Has anyone ever stayed at Pelican Landing resort in Morson? Looking for any info someone might have , Good or Bad. Looks like a nice little place to stay for a week. Thanks! Fred

My objection to this place would be its location. I have gone by it a few times and don't know anything, good or bad, about the operation.Due to its location, you could be exposed to some very rough water coming and going and if there is a big three day wind, which happens to me every few years, you probably won't be fishing at all.

I don't know a bunch about it, but it is in my area. If the winds were horrible, you could just launch your boat at the government dock for free and avoid the open water. It's a great fishing area, the new owners have had it for 2 years now.
Thanks for your help guys Dog
